<br>
People on this board have given some really good ideas before about ways to get around that.<br>
<br>
- JickyJack had the idea to have an idea jar.  Anytime you get a good idea of something to draw, write it down so you don't forget it and put it in a jar.  Then when you don't have music around or can't think of anything to draw, just tap into the jar for ideas.<br>
<br>
- if you can't think of anything interesting to draw, just go back to doing some basic practicing for the day.  Pull out some art books or anatomy books and just practice.  you can always come back to the other stuff later.<br>
<br>
- like linabo said, if you draw better with music on, then why aren't you listening to music more often silly?  just don't draw with it off. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ucaptainsnafu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CaptainSNAFU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/29/01 5:59:13 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://complabs.nevada.edu/~heff5131/inked_mecha_small_small.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: drawing w/inspiration</span><hr size=1> hey those are cool ideas!!! i like the jar one, and even though its boring i suppose the basic are kinda important........just a lil' bit <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
